270
00:31:53,607 --> 00:31:56,486
- You're losing your sense of proportion.
- But that's ridiculous.

271
00:31:56,608 --> 00:31:59,598
Perhaps it's time
you went out into the real world.

272
00:32:11,688 --> 00:32:15,440
(Connie) What does it matter?
Old Circus is gone anyway.

273
00:32:31,527 --> 00:32:33,484
Here we are.

274
00:32:33,608 --> 00:32:35,599
The Nursery in our day.

275
00:32:37,649 --> 00:32:39,526
Jim Prideaux.

276
00:32:39,649 --> 00:32:43,084
And Bill Haydon.
Together, of course.

277
00:32:43,887 --> 00:32:45,479
The Inseparables.

278
00:32:48,608 --> 00:32:50,564
There's Control himself.

279
00:32:51,648 --> 00:32:53,241
All my boys.

280
00:32:54,807 --> 00:32:57,162
All my lovely boys.

281
00:32:59,848 --> 00:33:01,998
That was a good time, George.

282
00:33:03,368 --> 00:33:05,485
It was the war, Connie.

283
00:33:08,327 --> 00:33:10,478
A real war.

284
00:33:10,608 --> 00:33:12,678
Englishmen could be proud then.

285
00:33:19,969 --> 00:33:22,322
So I was right, then?

286
00:33:22,447 --> 00:33:24,677
About Polyakov.

287
00:33:24,807 --> 00:33:26,560
There is a mole.

288
00:33:30,368 --> 00:33:35,284
If it's bad, don't come back.
I want to remember you all as you were.

289
00:33:37,888 --> 00:33:40,561
