out of the Circus.

672
01:07:55,878 --> 01:07:57,755
I should get some rest.

673
01:07:59,159 --> 01:08:01,434
I suppose you've got your reading to do.

674
01:08:02,838 --> 01:08:04,352
Come up.

675
01:08:15,959 --> 01:08:17,756
I met him once.

676
01:08:19,119 --> 01:08:20,597
Karla.

677
01:08:22,198 --> 01:08:23,517
In '55.

678
01:08:26,559 --> 01:08:28,754
Moscow Centre was in pieces.

679
01:08:30,760 --> 01:08:33,750
Purge after purge.

680
01:08:33,878 --> 01:08:36,154
Half their agents were jumping ship.

681
01:08:37,558 --> 01:08:39,674
I travelled around, signing them up.

682
01:08:41,159 --> 01:08:42,558
Hundreds of them.

683
01:08:46,079 --> 01:08:48,797
One of them
was calling himself Gerstmann.

684
01:08:49,678 --> 01:08:51,829
He was on his way back to Russia

685
01:08:51,959 --> 01:08:55,269
and we were pretty sure
he was going to be executed.

686
01:08:55,399 --> 01:08:59,712
Plane had a 24-hour lay-over at Delhi
and that's how long I had

687
01:08:59,840 --> 01:09:02,831
to convince him to come over to us

688
01:09:02,959 --> 01:09:04,950
instead of going home to die.

689
01:09:10,360 --> 01:09:12,077
There's a little room.

690
01:09:14,560 --> 01:09:17,948
I'm sitting here. He's sitting there.

691
01:09:22,399 --> 01:09:25,710
The Americans had had him tortured.

692
01:09:29,639 --> 01:09:31,630
