and we can give you a comfortable life,

698
01:10:01,360 --> 01:10:03,157
after questioning.

699
01:10:07,001 --> 01:10:08,719
What did he say?

700
01:10:13,640 --> 01:10:15,392
Think of your wife.

701
01:10:18,001 --> 01:10:20,037
You have a wife, don't you?

702
01:10:23,401 --> 01:10:26,197
Here. I brought you some cigarettes,
by the way.

703
01:10:30,200 --> 01:10:31,758
Use my lighter.

704
01:10:36,801 --> 01:10:41,749
We could arrange for her to join you.
We have a lot of stock to trade.

705
01:10:43,520 --> 01:10:46,752
If you go back, she'll be ostracised.
Think of her.

706
01:10:46,881 --> 01:10:48,519
Think about...

707
01:10:52,960 --> 01:10:54,518
I kept on...

708
01:10:55,841 --> 01:10:58,070
...harping on about the damn wife,

709
01:11:00,481 --> 01:11:02,517
telling him more about me than...

710
01:11:05,962 --> 01:11:07,951
I should have walked out, of course.

711
01:11:10,160 --> 01:11:14,279
But for some reason it seemed
important to save this one, so I go on.

712
01:11:17,042 --> 01:11:19,681
We're not so very different
you and I.

713
01:11:21,321 --> 01:11:22,834
We've both spent our lives

714
01:11:22,961 --> 01:11:26,192
looking for the weaknesses
in one another's systems.

715
01:11:29,282 --> 01:11:31,351
Don't you think it's time to recognise

716
01:11:31,481 --> 01:11:35,758
there is as little worth on your side
as there is on mine?

717
01:11:48,321 --> 01:11:50,312
Never said a word.

718
01:11:56,602 --> 01:11:58,354
Not one word.

719
01:12:07,161 --> 01:12:09,756
And the next morning
he got back on his plane.

720
01:12:11,202 --> 01:12:13,875
He handed the pack of cigarettes
back to me, untouched.

721
01:12:14,002 --> 01:12:17,880
This was a chain-smoker, mind.

722
01:12:18,001 --> 01:12:21,995
And he flew off to what
he presumed would be his death.

723
01:12:25,683 --> 01:12:27,514
He kept my lighter.

724
01:12:31,242 --> 01:12:32,834
It was a gift.

725
01:12:35,042 --> 01:12:37,034
To George from Ann.

726
01:12:39,483 --> 01:12:41,154
All my love.

727
01:12:44,201 --> 01:12:45,793
That was Karla.

728
01:12:47,962 --> 01:12:50,556
He went back to die
rather than giving in.

729
01:12:53,323 --> 01:12:55,962
Yes, and that's how I know
he can be beaten.

730
01:12:59,882 --> 01:13:01,873
Because he's a fanatic.

731
01:13:03,483 --> 01:13:07,078
And the fanatic is always
concealing a secret doubt.

732
01:13:12,642 --> 01:13:14,201
What did he look like?

733
01:13:16,362 --> 01:13:18,239
I can't remember.

734
01:13:38,964 --> 01:13:40,999
After today, Peter,

735
01:13:42,403 --> 01:13:44,758
you have to assume
they're watching you.

736
01:13:50,163 --> 01:13:52,314
If there's anything you need tidied up,

737
01:13:56,643 --> 01:13:58,440
now is the time.

738
01:14:12,324 --> 01:14:13,837
Nearly done.

739
01:14:15,204 --> 01:14:16,842
For God's sake.

740
01:14:20,605 --> 01:14:23,880
Sometimes I think they're all
sharing the same moronic brain.

741
01:14:34,365 --> 01:14:36,638
If there's someone else,
you can tell me.

742
01:14:39,124 --> 01:14:40,842
I'm a grown-up.

743
01:14:56,365 --> 01:14:57,764
(Door closes)

