He wanted someone he could trust.

766
01:17:31,007 --> 01:17:34,636
(Radio) Hurricane Henry set
to be ridden by Ray Walsh at 7:2'...

767
01:17:35,726 --> 01:17:38,798
- (Gunshot)
- (Shouting in Russian)

768
01:17:38,926 --> 01:17:42,203
(Tape clicking)

769
01:18:05,846 --> 01:18:07,565
There's been a bit of a panic, sir.

770
01:18:09,487 --> 01:18:11,921
This is from the FO resident clerk.

771
01:18:12,047 --> 01:18:14,437
A Hungarian news bulletin.

772
01:18:14,568 --> 01:18:16,638
British spy, work name Ellis,

773
01:18:16,768 --> 01:18:18,837
travelling with false Hungarian papers,

774
01:18:18,967 --> 01:18:23,439
has attempted to kidnap an unnamed
Hungarian General in Budapest.

775
01:18:24,528 --> 01:18:26,439
He's been shot.

776
01:18:26,568 --> 01:18:28,558
Other arrests imminent.

777
01:18:28,687 --> 01:18:30,280
(Phones ringing)

778
01:18:32,166 --> 01:18:34,158
Can I have a brief, please?

779
01:18:36,807 --> 01:18:39,241
Sir? Do you want me to deny it, sir?

780
01:18:39,367 --> 01:18:40,721
(Phones ringing)

781
01:18:44,927 --> 01:18:47,282
I must have a brief, sir.

782
01:18:47,407 --> 01:18:49,762
(Jerry) I couldn't get
a word out of Control.

783
01:18:49,887 --> 01:18:52,846
So I followed protocol
and went for the emergency list.

784
01:18:55,969 --> 01:18:57,960
You rang my house.

785
01:18:58,089 --> 01:19:00,476
Just on the off-chance
you were back from Berlin.

786
01:19:00,607 --> 01:19:01,961
What did you say?

787
01:19:02,807 --> 01:19:04,843
- Hello?
- Hello, Mrs. Smiley.

788
01:19:04,967 --> 01:19:06,959
It's Jerry.
Jerry Westerby from the office.

789
01:19:07,088 --> 01:19:09,283
Just that there'd been a bit of a crisis.

790
01:19:09,408 --> 01:19:11,399
Ann said you wasn't back yet
and that was it.

791
01:19:12,567 --> 01:19:13,602
Go on.

792
01:19:13,727 --> 01:19:15,206
All hell broke loose.

793
01:19:15,327 --> 01:19:17,637
Military yelling about
Hungarian tanks on the border.

794
01:19:17,768 --> 01:19:20,328
Lacon and the minister
baying at the door.

795
01:19:21,168 --> 01:19:23,763
Thank Christ
Bill Haydon turned up when he did.

796
01:19:23,889 --> 01:19:25,038
- Mr. Haydon.
- Not now.

797
01:19:25,169 --> 01:19:26,441
Mr. Haydon!

798
01:19:27,968 --> 01:19:28,923
Out!

799
01:19:30,768 --> 01:19:32,486
- Tell me.
- I tried to get hold of you.

800
01:19:32,608 --> 01:19:35,646
I got half a story
on the ticker tape at my club. Tell me.

801
01:19:36,809 --> 01:19:38,606
Jim Prideaux's been shot.

802
01:19:42,967 --> 01:19:44,799
Get me the Hungarian embassy.

803
01:19:44,928 --> 01:19:46,646
You tell your masters what will happen

804
01:19:46,768 --> 01:19:48,565
if one hair on Jim Prideaux's head
is damaged.

805
01:19:48,688 --> 01:19:51,487
Get Esterhase on the phone.
Tell him to call in the Hungarian agents.

806
01:19:51,609 --> 01:19:52,564
Yes, sir.

807
01:20:04,209 --> 01:20:06,644
Any more news on him? Sir?

808
01:20:11,409 --> 01:20:12,761
Oh, God.

809
01:20:12,888 --> 01:20:15,482
We need to get down to his flat,
clear out anything linked.

810
01:20:56,049 --> 01:20:58,928
(Guillam)
Haydon heard the news at his club?

811
01:20:59,050 --> 01:21:00,278
(Smiley) The Savile.

812
01:21:00,410 --> 01:21:03,208
(Guillam) At 1:30? The ticker-tape
wouldn't have been running.

813
01:21:03,330 --> 01:21:04,967
So how did he know?

814
01:21:06,489 --> 01:21:07,922
- Jesus, George.
- Peter!

815
01:21:08,049 --> 01:21:10,484
- How could he have known?
- It's not what you think.

816
01:21:10,610 --> 01:21:14,365
- Then how did he know?
- He was at my house that night.

817
01:21:43,251 --> 01:21:45,242
Good flight?

818
01:21:47,850 --> 01:21:49,681
Yes.

819
01:21:49,810 --> 01:21:51,687
Pleasant enough.

820
01:21:51,811 --> 01:21:53,608
I was just passing.
I thought I'd call in.

821
01:21:54,451 --> 01:21:57,602
Ann was in bed.
She insisted on getting up.

822
01:21:57,731 --> 01:21:59,879
She said she'd be down in a minute.

823
01:22:01,569 --> 01:22:04,960
That's what I'm dropping off.
It's an awful daub really.

824
01:22:06,610 --> 01:22:08,806
But Ann expressed a liking.

825
01:22:11,691 --> 01:22:13,521
What's keeping her?

826
01:22:29,531 --> 01:22:30,883
(Prideaux) Keep going.

827
01:22:32,010 --> 01:22:34,001
Come on, lads. Keep up.

828
01:22:36,851 --> 01:22:38,569
Come on, Bill!

829
01:22:51,132 --> 01:22:53,692
- Got your specs on, Jumbo?
- Yes, sir.

830
01:22:53,812 --> 01:22:55,402
Come here.

831
01:23:01,612 --> 01:23:03,603
Who's that fellow down there?

832
01:23:05,212 --> 01:23:07,328
I don't know, sir.

833
01:23:07,452 --> 01:23:09,441
Who is he?

834
01:23:09,570 --> 01:23:11,367
Beggar man?

835
01:23:11,490 --> 01:23:12,890
Thief?

836
01:23:14,451 --> 01:23:16,919
Why doesn't he look this way, hm?

837
01:23:17,051 --> 01:23:20,727
Wouldn't you if you saw a bunch
of boys flogging a car round a field?

838
01:23:21,892 --> 01:23:25,122
What's the matter with him?
Doesn't he like us?

839
01:23:25,251 --> 01:23:28,164
I don't hold with odd-bods
hanging around.

840
01:23:28,292 --> 01:23:30,760
He might steal the Alvis.

841
01:23:30,892 --> 01:23:33,122
- Which is?
- The best car in England, sir.

842
01:23:36,571 --> 01:23:38,084
Good lad.

843
01:23:47,092 --> 01:23:50,925
(Smiley) How were you briefed
for the Budapest mission?

844
01:23:51,051 --> 01:23:53,963
(Prideaux) Control asked me
to come to a flat in Kensington.

845
01:23:56,412 --> 01:23:58,972
There's a rotten apple, Jim.

846
01:24:00,893 --> 01:24:02,884
And we have to find it.

847
01:24:04,771 --> 01:24:07,844
What did you make of it, Jim?

848
01:24:07,972 --> 01:24:09,849
Control's theory?

849
01:24:11,333 --> 01:24:13,847
I thought it was madness.

850
01:24:13,973 --> 01:24:18,203
I know that it is one of five men.

851
01:24:19,691 --> 01:24:23,287
All I want from you is one code name.

852
01:24:30,013 --> 01:24:31,412
Alleline.

853
01:24:33,612 --> 01:24:35,125
Tinker.

854
01:24:35,812 --> 01:24:37,211
Haydon.

855
01:24:38,893 --> 01:24:40,406
Tailor.

856
01:24:42,053 --> 01:24:43,453
Bland.

857
01:24:45,894 --> 01:24:47,291
Soldier.

858
01:24:48,693 --> 01:24:51,411
We drop Sailor.
It's too close to Tailor.

859
01:24:51,532 --> 01:24:53,603
And Rich Man doesn't seem
to be applicable.

860
01:24:55,573 --> 01:24:56,972
Esterhase.

861
01:24:58,814 --> 01:25:01,007
Poor Man.

862
01:25:06,213 --> 01:25:07,771
And the fifth?

863
01:25:09,974 --> 01:25:11,407
Smiley.

864
01:25:15,133 --> 01:25:17,124
I thought it was madness.

865
01:25:18,493 --> 01:25:21,486
To think that any one of you
could have been a traitor.

866
01:25:22,974 --> 01:25:24,565
Absolute madness.

867
01:25:26,494 --> 01:25:29,211
(Smiley) But you still went.

868
01:25:29,332 --> 01:25:31,403
Why?

869
01:25:31,533 --> 01:25:34,570
(Prideaux) I went
because Control asked me to go.

870
01:25:34,693 --> 01:25:37,083
It's called doing one's duty.

871
01:25:47,734 --> 01:25:52,411
At the station I met the legman
supposed to take me to the General.

872
01:25:52,535 --> 01:25:54,491
The waiter must have panicked.

873
01:25:54,615 --> 01:25:56,410
It was meant to be
a simple snatch job.

874
01:26:02,894 --> 01:26:05,362
They drove me
to some military hospital,

875
01:26:05,494 --> 01:26:08,167
and then put me on a transport plane.

876
01:26:08,295 --> 01:26:10,488
I could tell by the stars
we were heading east.

877
01:26:14,814 --> 01:26:16,805
Then they worked me for...

878
01:26:16,934 --> 01:26:18,926
(Sighs heavily)

879
01:26:19,055 --> 01:26:21,410
I don't know how long.

880
01:26:21,535 --> 01:26:23,683
Weeks, maybe months.

881
01:26:24,854 --> 01:26:27,766
(Cacophony of sounds
start and stop)

882
01:27:02,416 --> 01:27:04,088
What did you tell them?

883
01:27:05,534 --> 01:27:07,093
Everything.

884
01:27:09,294 --> 01:27:13,049
I held on for as long as I could to let
everyone get the hell out of there.

885
01:27:15,135 --> 01:27:16,534
Did they?

886
01:27:17,655 --> 01:27:20,327
My networks in Hungary,
did they get out?

887
01:27:22,974 --> 01:27:24,966
No, they were blown.

888
01:27:27,095 --> 01:27:30,611
The story is you blew them
to save your own skin.

889
01:27:33,815 --> 01:27:35,407
(Shouting in Russian)

890
01:27:37,855 --> 01:27:42,646
After the interrogators had cleared out,
this little fellow turned up.

891
01:27:44,616 --> 01:27:46,493
Looked like a priest.

892
01:27:47,934 --> 01:27:50,210
That's when they really started on me.

893
01:27:50,335 --> 01:27:53,805
What was your last line of defence, hm?

894
01:27:55,336 --> 01:27:56,928
The mole.

895
01:27:58,256 --> 01:28:00,247
Control's crazy theory.

896
01:28:02,255 --> 01:28:05,645
I was going to bury that so deep
they'd never get it out of me.

897
01:28:07,496 --> 01:28:10,249
- Which was a joke.
- Why?

898
01:28:11,857 --> 01:28:14,132
Because they already knew.

899
01:28:14,257 --> 01:28:17,646
All they wanted to know was how far
Control had got in his investigation.

900
01:28:32,736 --> 01:28:34,488
No, I don't know her.

901
01:28:49,977 --> 01:28:51,615
(Door closes)

902
01:28:54,137 --> 01:28:57,127
Did they ask about me at all?

903
01:28:57,255 --> 01:28:58,654
Yes.

904
01:28:59,656 --> 01:29:01,533
The little fellow did.

905
01:29:03,736 --> 01:29:06,535
What did he say about me?

906
01:29:08,057 --> 01:29:10,172
He had this cigarette lighter.

907
01:29:11,576 --> 01:29:14,170
He kept flashing it about
for me to see it.

908
01:29:15,417 --> 01:29:17,567
Showed me the inscription.

909
01:29:17,697 --> 01:29:19,813
- To George...
- From Ann.

910
01:29:21,218 --> 01:29:22,856
All my love.

911
01:29:28,496 --> 01:29:29,895
Karla.

912
01:29:44,137 --> 01:29:45,490
(Gunshot)

913
01:29:47,338 --> 01:29:49,329
(Baby crying)

914
01:29:59,458 --> 01:30:01,449
(Prideaux) It was odd.

915
01:30:02,857 --> 01:30:05,326
They sent me back to England.

916
01:30:05,456 --> 01:30:07,890
Straight to Sarratt for debriefing.

917
01:30:10,617 --> 01:30:15,408
He said when he was being debriefed
at the Nursery, he had a visitor.

918
01:30:15,538 --> 01:30:16,607
Who?

919
01:30:16,738 --> 01:30:19,535
(Smiley) Toby Esterhase.

920
01:30:19,657 --> 01:30:22,217
He gave him £1,000 and an Alvis.

921
01:30:23,217 --> 01:30:26,415
Told him he was dead now.
Couldn't come back.

922
01:30:26,538 --> 01:30:29,848
Had to become a lotus eater,
forget everything that happened.

923
01:30:29,978 --> 01:30:31,776
Control's theory.

924
01:30:31,899 --> 01:30:34,013
Tinker, Tailor. All of it.

925
01:30:35,418 --> 01:30:37,931
Yes, that's what I thought.

926
01:30:38,057 --> 01:30:42,176
How on earth did Esterhase
hear about Tinker, Tailor?

927
01:30:58,099 --> 01:31:00,215
(Tarr on tape) Irina kept telling me
in Moscow Centre...

928
01:31:00,339 --> 01:31:03,535
everybody on the top floor
was laughing themselves sick.

929
01:31:03,658 --> 01:31:05,967
She told me
Karla was very proud of this.

930
01:31:06,098 --> 01:31:09,171
She said everything the Circus thinks
is gold is shit, made in Moscow.

931
01:31:14,579 --> 01:31:16,613
Irina kept telling me
in Moscow Centre...

932
01:31:16,737 --> 01:31:19,536
everybody on the top floor
was laughing themselves sick.

933
01:31:19,658 --> 01:31:22,695
No, I had a hotel nearby.
They do have some seedy rooms.

934
01:31:22,818 --> 01:31:24,775
Irina kept telling me in Moscow Centre

935
01:31:24,899 --> 01:31:28,289
everybody on the top floor
was laughing themselves sick.

936
01:31:28,419 --> 01:31:30,295
She told me
Karla was very proud of this'...

937
01:31:30,418 --> 01:31:35,334
(Tape recording on a loop)

938
01:32:05,419 --> 01:32:07,729
She said everything
the Circus thinks is gold is shit.

939
01:32:07,860 --> 01:32:09,657
(Stops tape)

940
01:32:36,780 --> 01:32:39,851
This meeting is not taking place.
Is that clear?

941
01:32:40,979 --> 01:32:42,537
Perfectly, Minister.

942
01:32:47,180 --> 01:32:52,016
There is a house
somewhere in this city

943
01:32:53,059 --> 01:32:56,654
where Alleline and the others meet
Witchcraft's London representative.

944
01:32:56,779 --> 01:32:58,815
I thought Lacon had made it
clear to you.

945
01:32:58,939 --> 01:33:02,410
Keep your nose bloody well
out of Witchcraft's business.

946
01:33:02,540 --> 01:33:04,292
It's Lacon's advice I'm following.

947
01:33:04,420 --> 01:33:06,887
You told me
to follow in Control's footsteps.

948
01:33:07,019 --> 01:33:11,491
I wouldn't consider that sound advice,
given the mess Control left us with.

949
01:33:12,580 --> 01:33:16,620
It has taken Alleline
and, if I may say so, myself

950
01:33:16,741 --> 01:33:18,697
this long to get us back in the game.

951
01:33:19,821 --> 01:33:23,608
The man Alleline and the others
meet is called Polyakov.

952
01:33:26,100 --> 01:33:28,774
You believe his role
is to bring information

953
01:33:28,901 --> 01:33:30,891
from Witchcraft to you.

954
01:33:31,020 --> 01:33:35,695
His real role is to receive
information from the mole

955
01:33:35,819 --> 01:33:37,333
to take back to Karla.

956
01:33:38,660 --> 01:33:41,891
That, er...
That's not possible.

957
01:33:42,020 --> 01:33:43,613
Made possible.

958
01:33:43,741 --> 01:33:47,017
By you in the house you persuaded
the Treasury to pay for.

959
01:33:47,860 --> 01:33:52,854
Witchcraft's intelligence is genuine.
It's been gold.

960
01:33:52,980 --> 01:33:57,099
It's just enough glitter
amongst the chicken feed.

961
01:33:57,221 --> 01:33:59,975
Control didn't believe in miracles
or in Witchcraft.

962
01:34:00,102 --> 01:34:01,818
But you were lazy and greedy

963
01:34:01,940 --> 01:34:05,819
and so you hounded him
out of the Circus and you let Karla in.

964
01:34:08,420 --> 01:34:12,460
You opened negotiations to exchange
intelligence with the Americans.

965
01:34:12,581 --> 01:34:16,095
What they tell the Circus,
they'll be telling the Kremlin.

966
01:34:16,220 --> 01:34:21,454
Witchcraft's information,
the gold Karla let you have,

967
01:34:21,581 --> 01:34:23,617
it wasn't to lure you.

968
01:34:23,741 --> 01:34:25,937
It was to lure the Americans.

969
01:34:27,982 --> 01:34:29,652
Now,

970
01:34:29,780 --> 01:34:31,772
do you want to take credit for that?

971
01:34:36,102 --> 01:34:37,899
What can we do?

972
01:34:40,221 --> 01:34:43,849
We have one thing the mole wants.

973
01:34:46,941 --> 01:34:48,215
- If I go to Paris...
- You'll go.

974
01:34:48,341 --> 01:34:51,014
If I go to Paris,

975
01:34:52,702 --> 01:34:55,091
I want your word
that you will get Irina back.

976
01:34:56,582 --> 01:35:00,017
I don't care who you have to trade.
And I am out.

977
01:35:02,461 --> 01:35:06,535
I want a family, thank you.
I do not want to end up like you lot.

978
01:35:06,662 --> 01:35:08,893
You will get her back.

979
01:35:11,661 --> 01:35:14,051
I'll do my utmost, Ricki.

980
01:35:15,741 --> 01:35:17,538
(Metallic clanging)

981
01:35:38,063 --> 01:35:40,053
Oh, hello, George.

982
01:35:41,182 --> 01:35:42,581
Hello.

983
01:36:07,462 --> 01:36:09,771
I want to talk about loyalty, Toby.

984
01:36:12,663 --> 01:36:15,541
Control recruited you, didn't he?

985
01:36:15,663 --> 01:36:18,701
Found you starving
in a museum in Vienna.

986
01:36:18,824 --> 01:36:21,211
A wanted man.

987
01:36:21,342 --> 01:36:23,334
Saved your life, I heard.

988
01:36:24,422 --> 01:36:26,492
And yet when the time came,

989
01:36:26,622 --> 01:36:28,898
when it came to picking sides
between him and Alleline,

990
01:36:29,023 --> 01:36:30,900
you didn't hesitate.

991
01:36:31,903 --> 01:36:35,497
That's understandable, perhaps,
with your war experience.

992
01:36:35,622 --> 01:36:40,174
You survived this long, I suppose,
because of your ability to change sides.

993
01:36:40,303 --> 01:36:42,294
Serve any master.

994
01:36:47,704 --> 01:36:50,297
What? What's...
What's this about, George?

995
01:36:51,343 --> 01:36:54,460
It's about which master
you've been serving, Toby.

996
01:36:58,304 --> 01:37:00,772
(Smiley) Intelligence
has been leaked, Toby.

997
01:37:00,904 --> 01:37:03,655
Someone's been taking files
from the Circus.

998
01:37:03,782 --> 01:37:05,933
(Esterhase) No, no, no, no. No.

999
01:37:06,063 --> 01:37:07,735
This is a mistake, a misunderstanding.

1000
01:37:07,863 --> 01:37:11,140
Files were delivered
to a Russian attaché, weren't they?

1001
01:37:11,264 --> 01:37:12,379
Yes.

1002
01:37:14,144 --> 01:37:16,737
(Esterhase) And, yes, I delivered them.

1003
01:37:16,863 --> 01:37:19,502
(Speaks Russian)

1004
01:37:22,024 --> 01:37:24,219
But so did Percy Alleline.

1005
01:37:28,905 --> 01:37:30,131
Good boy.

1006
01:37:30,263 --> 01:37:32,255
(Esterhase) Bill Haydon.

1007
01:37:33,943 --> 01:37:35,934
And so did Roy Bland.

1008
01:37:45,343 --> 01:37:47,732
Things aren't always
what they seem, George.

1009
01:37:47,863 --> 01:37:49,741
You should know that.

1010
01:37:49,864 --> 01:37:52,219
Look, Moscow thinks Polyakov's...

1011
01:37:56,265 --> 01:37:58,174
...working for them.

1012
01:37:58,303 --> 01:38:00,738
Every now and then we give him
the odd file to take back to them.

1013
01:38:00,864 --> 01:38:03,173
Chicken feed,
just to keep his bosses happy.

1014
01:38:05,505 --> 01:38:08,621
But Polyakov's our Joe.

1015
01:38:08,744 --> 01:38:12,292
- He's a part of a big operation.
- Operation Witchcraft.

1016
01:38:13,223 --> 01:38:14,656
Yes, I know.

1017
01:38:15,624 --> 01:38:17,216
George.

1018
01:38:17,344 --> 01:38:20,063
- Please, I don't deserve this.
- Who gave you the message

1019
01:38:20,185 --> 01:38:22,779
for Jim Prideaux
to forget about Tinker, Tailor?

1020
01:38:22,905 --> 01:38:25,100
- Bland.
- To get rid of Connie Sachs?

1021
01:38:25,225 --> 01:38:26,896
- Westerby?
- Bland.

1022
01:38:27,024 --> 01:38:29,140
Or Haydon.

1023
01:38:29,264 --> 01:38:30,983
I don't know. One of them.

1024
01:38:32,185 --> 01:38:33,982
Or maybe Percy. No.

1025
01:38:34,105 --> 01:38:36,700
Well, I don't know who.

1026
01:38:36,826 --> 01:38:38,942
You're just the messenger.

1027
01:38:39,984 --> 01:38:42,499
Running between them all.

1028
01:38:42,625 --> 01:38:44,979
Anything to serve Witchcraft.

1029
01:38:46,224 --> 01:38:48,500
I know all about your secret source.

1030
01:38:50,185 --> 01:38:52,176
And I know something you don't.

1031
01:38:54,104 --> 01:38:56,174
I know who he is.

1032
01:38:58,465 --> 01:39:00,456
He's Karla.

1033
01:39:01,225 --> 01:39:04,457
(Plane engine revs)

1034
01:39:07,904 --> 01:39:12,103
(Smiley) One of you has been giving
Polyakov the crown jewels.

1035
01:39:12,225 --> 01:39:15,263
- I did not know.
- Are you still a wanted man, Toby?

1036
01:39:15,386 --> 01:39:19,095
- Look, George, I didn't know. I...
- You picked the wrong side.

1037
01:39:19,226 --> 01:39:21,023
No, you've got to believe me.

1038
01:39:21,144 --> 01:39:23,374
George, please.

1039
01:39:27,345 --> 01:39:29,415
I am loyal.

1040
01:39:30,146 --> 01:39:32,376
I... I am loyal.

1041
01:39:42,986 --> 01:39:45,341
Don't... Don't...
Don't send me back.

1042
01:39:45,466 --> 01:39:47,264
Please, George.

1043
01:39:48,107 --> 01:39:49,777
Don't send me back.

1044
01:39:55,065 --> 01:39:57,057
Give me the address.

1045
01:40:00,146 --> 01:40:02,456
Where do you meet Polyakov?

1046
01:40:12,947 --> 01:40:14,096
(Radio on)

1047
01:40:14,227 --> 01:40:15,342
(Knocking)

1048
01:40:15,467 --> 01:40:17,695
Hey, hey!
Dog, dog, be quiet!

1049
01:40:18,786 --> 01:40:21,459
What is this? Who are you?

1050
01:40:21,586 --> 01:40:23,384
- Mrs. McCraig?
- Yes.

1051
01:40:38,466 --> 01:40:40,776
- What are the safety signals?
- The air vent.

1052
01:40:40,907 --> 01:40:43,216
Open and all's well,
closed and you're not to enter.

1053
01:40:46,626 --> 01:40:48,821
And the microphone?

1054
01:40:55,468 --> 01:40:56,787
Peter?

1055
01:41:12,706 --> 01:41:15,584
The boy stood on the burning deck
whence all but he had fled

1056
01:41:15,706 --> 01:41:18,016
The flame that lit the battle's wreck
shone brightly o'er the dead

1057
01:41:18,947 --> 01:41:22,224
(Tape) Beautiful and proud he stood
as born to rule the storm

1058
01:41:22,348 --> 01:41:25,465
A creature of blood,
a proud though child-like form

1059
01:41:25,588 --> 01:41:28,147
- The flames rolled on...
- (Knocking)

1060
01:41:30,587 --> 01:41:32,897
(Bells chime)

1061
01:41:38,868 --> 01:41:41,664
Merci. Au revoir.

1062
01:42:02,708 --> 01:42:05,507
(Speak French)

1063
01:42:13,467 --> 01:42:14,946
Go on.

1064
01:42:22,547 --> 01:42:24,458
The whole service is looking for you.

1065
01:42:24,587 --> 01:42:27,819
- They'll skin you alive if they find you.
- Maybe I want them to find me.

1066
01:42:29,468 --> 01:42:32,541
You can go now. Leave the books
and put the keys in the machines.

1067
01:42:32,669 --> 01:42:35,183
No, Ben stays here.

1068
01:42:35,309 --> 01:42:40,462
Ricki Tarr claims to have information
vital to the safeguarding of the Circus.

1069
01:43:01,829 --> 01:43:03,625
(Mendel) Mr. Smiley?

1070
01:43:06,028 --> 01:43:07,381
Taxi approaching Circus.

1071
01:43:19,268 --> 01:43:20,668
Tinker.

1072
01:43:31,110 --> 01:43:32,826
Tailor.

1073
01:43:37,909 --> 01:43:39,581
Here comes Soldier.

1074
01:43:44,150 --> 01:43:45,706
Full house.

1075
01:43:57,990 --> 01:44:03,541
- Well, go on then. Read it out loud.
- Personal for Tarr from Alleline.

1076
01:44:04,629 --> 01:44:08,828
Require clarification
before meeting your request.

1077
01:44:09,830 --> 01:44:15,665
Quote, information vital to safeguarding
of the Circus, unquote...

1078
01:44:16,909 --> 01:44:20,983
does not qualify,
send further information.

1079
01:44:21,110 --> 01:44:24,103
Ah! That's it, Percy,
you keep stalling.

1080
01:44:24,231 --> 01:44:26,948
I warn you, Ben. We've got
some really lousy people in this outfit.

1081
01:44:27,069 --> 01:44:29,186
I wouldn't trust a fucking one of them.

1082
01:44:36,750 --> 01:44:38,866
(Mendel) The meeting's over.

1083
01:44:41,189 --> 01:44:43,020
They're leaving.

1084
01:45:04,431 --> 01:45:06,387
(Car approaches and stops)

1085
01:45:06,511 --> 01:45:08,229
(Car door slams)

1086
01:45:12,950 --> 01:45:15,510
(Footsteps)

1087
01:45:15,630 --> 01:45:16,665
(Door closes)

1088
01:45:16,790 --> 01:45:18,622
(Footsteps)

1089
01:48:34,513 --> 01:48:36,630
Craddox says I'll be off in a few days.

1090
01:48:38,352 --> 01:48:41,948
I keep thinking how much
I'm going to miss the cricket in Moscow.

1091
01:48:48,394 --> 01:48:52,671
I was rather hoping you might do
a little light housekeeping for me.

1092
01:48:54,393 --> 01:48:55,986
If I can.

1093
01:48:56,714 --> 01:49:01,105
There's a girl.
Give her some money, would you?

1094
01:49:01,234 --> 01:49:03,351
And give her a good cover story.

1095
01:49:05,513 --> 01:49:08,186
If it helps, tell her I love her.

1096
01:49:08,313 --> 01:49:09,985
It's all there.

1097
01:49:10,113 --> 01:49:13,993
And there's a boy, too.
Slip him a few quid to shut him up.

1098
01:49:16,234 --> 01:49:20,112
I know the inquisitors' bag of tricks.
I taught most of them.

1099
01:49:22,674 --> 01:49:24,665
It's just a reaction.

1100
01:49:26,514 --> 01:49:28,949
An over-reaction, if you like.

1101
01:49:29,075 --> 01:49:31,635
I did have one or two questions.

1102
01:49:35,354 --> 01:49:37,151
- About Prideaux.
- Goddamn it!

1103
01:49:37,274 --> 01:49:40,073
- I got him back, didn't i?
- Yes, yes, you did.

1104
01:49:40,195 --> 01:49:42,072
That was good of you.

1105
01:49:43,114 --> 01:49:46,230
I am surprised
Karla didn't have him shot.

1106
01:49:47,713 --> 01:49:50,353
Or do you think he held back,

1107
01:49:50,474 --> 01:49:52,942
out of delicacy towards you?

1108
01:49:56,475 --> 01:50:00,911
Did Prideaux come and see you
before he left on the Hungarian mission?

1109
01:50:03,314 --> 01:50:05,590
Yes, as a matter of fact he did.

1110
01:50:08,115 --> 01:50:10,071
To say what?

1111
01:50:15,314 --> 01:50:17,112
To warn you.

1112
01:50:18,954 --> 01:50:21,422
Because he knew deep down

1113
01:50:22,595 --> 01:50:24,426
it was you all along.

1114
01:50:28,794 --> 01:50:30,989
So did you.

1115
01:50:34,835 --> 01:50:37,144
I had to pick a side, George.

1116
01:50:38,756 --> 01:50:41,905
It was an aesthetic choice
as much as a moral one.

1117
01:50:43,235 --> 01:50:46,147
And the West has become
so very ugly.

1118
01:50:47,275 --> 01:50:48,914
Don't you think?

1119
01:50:50,556 --> 01:50:53,992
Did Karla ever consider
having you take over the Circus?

1120
01:50:54,116 --> 01:50:56,344
I'm not his bloody office boy!

1121
01:50:56,474 --> 01:50:58,864
What are you, then, Bill?

1122
01:51:05,236 --> 01:51:07,431
I'm someone who's made his mark.

1123
01:51:20,597 --> 01:51:25,066
Is there anything particular
you want me to pass on to Ann?

1124
01:51:28,675 --> 01:51:33,033
Oh, that was nothing personal, George.
I hope you understand that.

1125
01:51:33,156 --> 01:51:35,351
Karla said you were good,

1126
01:51:35,476 --> 01:51:38,512
the one we had to worry about.

1127
01:51:38,635 --> 01:51:41,946
But you do have a blind spot.

1128
01:51:42,076 --> 01:51:44,351
He reckoned
if I was known to be Ann's lover,

1129
01:51:45,676 --> 01:51:48,555
you wouldn't be able to see me straight.

1130
01:51:50,077 --> 01:51:51,872
And he was right.

1131
01:51:53,236 --> 01:51:55,113
Up to a point.

1132
01:51:58,477 --> 01:52:00,195
Up to a point.

1133
01:52:15,757 --> 01:52:18,066
(Bill knocks)

1134
01:52:26,277 --> 01:52:28,154
I made this for you, sir.

1135
01:52:36,596 --> 01:52:39,588
I don't want you
hanging around here any more.

1136
01:52:41,317 --> 01:52:43,433
Keep away from me from now on.

1137
01:52:44,757 --> 01:52:47,224
- Go and join the others.
- But...

1138
01:52:47,356 --> 01:52:50,154
Just... just bloody join in, will you?

1139
01:52:53,677 --> 01:52:56,111
Go and play, damn you!

1140
01:53:06,197 --> 01:53:07,995
(♪ Musical intro)

1141
01:53:08,118 --> 01:53:11,189
(Singer introduces song in French)

1142
01:53:12,918 --> 01:53:15,476
Could you check, Jerry?

1143
01:53:29,317 --> 01:53:32,707
(♪ Sings La Mer in French)

1144
01:53:36,918 --> 01:53:39,113
(Applause)

1145
01:54:14,958 --> 01:54:17,189
(♪ Singing continues...)

1146
01:56:19,520 --> 01:56:21,954
(Song ends)

1147
01:56:22,080 --> 01:56:24,594
(Applause)

